
[1]mysticism

   MYS'TICISM, n. Obscurity of doctrine.

   1. The doctrine of the Mystics, who profess a pure, sublime and perfect
   devotion, wholly disinterested, and maintain that they hold immediate
   intercourse with the divine Spirit.
